/* cc.c
 *
 * Minimal educational single-file C compiler (amalgamated).
 * - Preprocessor: minimal (#include "file", #define simple)
 * - Lexer: identifiers, numbers, punctuation, keywords (int, char, struct, return)
 * - Parser: declarations, functions, blocks, expressions, struct definitions and member access
 * - Simple JIT codegen for x86-64 (emit machine code into executable mmap)
 * - Minimal ELF relocatable object writer for -c
 *
 * This file is written to avoid compiler warnings with -Wall -Wextra.
 *
 * Build:
 *   gcc -std=c99 -Wall -Wextra -O0 cc.c -o cc
 *
 * Usage:
 *   cc test.c            # JIT run main if present
 *   cc -c test.c -o test.o
 *
 * Notes:
 *  - This is intentionally minimal and educational.
 *  - The ELF writer produces a tiny relocatable object with .text and symbol table.
 */

